<seg id=1> Guangxi Utilizes Foreign Funds to Construct Communications and Shipping Infrastructure </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Nanning, March 14. (Reporter Lu Hankui) According to information from the Communications Department of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, so far Guangxi has made use of $0.15 billion loans from Bank of World, Bank of Asia as well as from Holand, South Korea, etc. to construct communications and shipping infrastructure. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> In recent years, China has sped up the construction of Southwest China's pasageway to the Sea, which goes through Guangxi. </seg>
<seg id=4> In order to solve the problem of financial insufficiency, and to open wider to the outside world,  Guangxi has made great effort to introduce foreign funds. </seg>
<seg id=5> In the Xijiang shipping hub phase II project, which will be invested a total of more than 2 billion RMB, $80 million loan from Bank of World has been used. At present, 80% of the principal part of the project has been dug out; 50% of the concrete casting amount has been completed. </seg>
<seg id=6> In the Fangchenggang City phase II project (including the highway from Qinzhou City to Fangchenggang City), $52 million loan from Asian Development Bank has been used. It is expected that the highway will be completed and put to use in the latter half of this year. </seg>
<seg id=7> In the program to construct the auxiliary facilities in Beihai Port, $10 million loan from South Korean Government has been used. </seg>
<seg id=8> In the program to construct the auxiliary facilities in Qinzhou Port, $13 million loan from Holand Government has been used. </seg>
<seg id=9> The constructions of these projects have been going smoothly. </seg>
</p>
